&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/mozilla/standards-positions/issues/896"&gt;https://github.com/mozilla/standards-positions/issues/896&lt;/a&gt;)
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; *WebKit*: No signal (
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/WebKit/standards-positions/issues/261"&gt;https://github.com/WebKit/standards-positions/issues/261&lt;/a&gt;)
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; *Web developers*: Positive (
&gt;&gt;&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://utilitybend.com/blog/is-the-sticky-thing-stuck-is-the-snappy-item-snapped-a-look-at-state-queries-in-css"&gt;https://utilitybend.com/blog/is-the-sticky-thing-stuck-is-the-snappy-item-snapped-a-look-at-state-queries-in-css&lt;/a&gt;)
&gt;&gt;&gt; Also, &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://ishadeed.com/article/css-state-queries/"&gt;https://ishadeed.com/article/css-state-queries/&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt;
&gt;&gt;&gt; *Other signals*:
&gt;&gt;&gt;
