&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/11183"&gt;https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/11183&lt;/a&gt;
&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/11127"&gt;https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/11127&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;
&gt; The one that's blocking shipping is the potential renaming from
&gt; 'overflowing' to 'scrollable':
&gt; &lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/11182"&gt;https://github.com/w3c/csswg-drafts/issues/11182&lt;/a&gt;
&gt;

This has now been resolved.

Two of the others are convenience keyword additions, and the last one is a
&gt; non-behavioral editorial change to the spec.
&gt;

11181 and 11183 have been scheduled for async resolution.

-- 
Rune Lillesveen

